            <h3>First Order Linear Differential Equations</h3>
            <h4>Leibnitz Equation</h4>
            
            <p>The standard form is:</p>
            <div class="math-display">
                $$\frac{dy}{dx} + P(x)y = Q(x)$$
            </div>
            <p>where $$P(x)$$ and $$Q(x)$$ are functions of $$x$$.</p>
            
            <div class="example">
                <h5>Solution Method</h5>
                <p>We use an <span class="highlight">Integrating Factor (I.F.)</span>:</p>
                <div class="math-display">
                    $$\text{I.F.} = e^{\int P(x)dx}$$
                </div>
                <p>The general solution is:</p>
                <div class="math-display">
                    $$y \cdot (\text{I.F.}) = \int Q(x) \cdot (\text{I.F.}) dx + C$$
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <details>
                <summary>Example: $$x\frac{dy}{dx} - (y-3x^2) = 0$$</summary>
                <div class="solution">
                    <p>Rearranging: $$x\frac{dy}{dx} - y = -3x^2$$</p>
                    <p>Dividing by $$x$$:</p>
                    <div class="math-display">
                        $$\frac{dy}{dx} - \frac{1}{x}y = -3x$$
                    </div>
                    <p>This is a first-order linear DE with $$P(x) = -\frac{1}{x}$$ and $$Q(x) = -3x$$.</p>
                    
                    <div class="steps">
                        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Find the Integrating Factor</p>
                        <div class="math-display">
                            $$\text{I.F.} = e^{\int -\frac{1}{x}dx} = e^{-\ln(x)} = \frac{1}{x}$$
                        </div>
                        
                        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Apply the solution formula</p>
                        <div class="math-display">
                            $$y \cdot \frac{1}{x} = \int (-3x) \cdot \frac{1}{x} dx + C = \int -3 dx + C = -3x + C$$
                        </div>
                        
                        <p><strong>General Solution:</strong> $$\frac{y}{x} + 3x = C$$</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </details>
            
