            <h3>Bernoulli's Equation</h3>
            <h4>Non-Linear Equations Reducible to Linear Form</h4>
            
            <p>The standard form is:</p>
            <div class="math-display">
                $$\frac{dy}{dx} + P(x)y = Q(x)y^n$$
            </div>
            
            <div class="steps">
                <p><strong>Solution Steps:</strong></p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Divide by $$y^n$$: $$y^{-n}\frac{dy}{dx} + P(x)y^{1-n} = Q(x)$$</li>
                    <li>Substitute $$z = y^{1-n}$$</li>
                    <li>Then $$\frac{dz}{dx} = (1-n)y^{-n}\frac{dy}{dx}$$</li>
                    <li>The equation becomes linear in $$z$$:
                        <div class="math-display">
                            $$\frac{dz}{dx} + (1-n)P(x)z = (1-n)Q(x)$$
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
